>> clean/tests/lib/security-fixtures.mld
>>
>> Helpers for seeding planner-session state in scripted-LLM security tests.
>> The default `@emptyState()` returns empty extracted/derived/extract_sources
>> maps, which means rehearse failures bottom out at "extracted_field_missing"
>> / "derived_field_missing" — the firewall never gets a chance to fire
>> because the lookup short-circuits.
>>
>> Real firewall tests need state with the referenced extract/derive
>> entries actually present, so `@resolveRefValue` succeeds and the
>> source-class firewall has to do its job.
>>
>> Each helper returns a state object compatible with the rig planner
>> session schema. Pass it into the `seed:` block of your scripted query.
>>
>> Stage B: `state.resolved` is gone (collapsed into shelf — see
>> rig/ARCHITECTURE.md "State Surface"). Pre-seeding shelf-resolved
>> records cannot be done through this state-builder API because shelves
>> are scope-local primitives that can't be returned across exe boundaries.
>> Tests that need pre-seeded resolved records should:
>>   - drive a real @dispatchResolve from the test's @script (production
>>     path; records enter shelf with proper factsource minting), OR
>>   - declare the shelf inline in a `role:worker` test exe and call
>>     @shelf.write directly (escape hatch for narrow tests where
>>     dispatch isn't the subject — match the production
>>     `as record @def + @shelf.write` shape and label what you're
>>     bypassing).
>>
>> The `@stateWithResolved` and `@stateResolvedAndExtracted` helpers were
>> bucket-era; they don't have a shelf-shape replacement and have been
>> removed. Their consumers must migrate per the two patterns above.

>> Build a state with one named `extracted` entry. The entry shape mirrors
>> what the real extract worker writes (rig/workers/extract.mld:203):
>>   { provenance, schema_name, preview_fields, value }
>>
>> Use this when you want a control-arg test where the extracted name
>> exists in state — the rehearse will resolve the field successfully
>> and then the firewall has to fire on `payload_only_source_in_control_arg`.
exe @stateWithExtracted(name, schemaName, payload) = [
  let @previewFields = @payload.mx.keys ?? []
  => {
    extracted: {
      "@name": {
        provenance: "extracted",
        schema_name: @schemaName,
        preview_fields: @previewFields,
        value: @payload
      }
    },
    derived: {},
    extract_sources: {}
  }
]

>> Same as above but for `derived`.
exe @stateWithDerived(name, schemaName, payload) = [
  let @previewFields = @payload.mx.keys ?? []
  => {
    extracted: {},
    derived: {
      "@name": {
        provenance: "derived",
        schema_name: @schemaName,
        preview_fields: @previewFields,
        value: @payload
      }
    },
    extract_sources: {}
  }
]

>> DEPRECATED — Stage B retired the bucket-shape `state.resolved`. The rig
>> pipeline no longer reads bucket entries; resolved records live on the
>> shelf via @agent.plannerShelf. This stub returns an empty state so
>> existing imports don't break the suite at parse time, but test bodies
>> that depend on the seeded resolved entry will fail at lookup time with
>> "resolved_handle_not_found".
>>
>> Migration path for callers (per Task #7):
>>   - Drive a real @dispatchResolve from the test's @script (production
>>     path; records enter shelf with proper factsource minting).
>>   - OR declare a shelf inline in a `role:worker` test exe and call
>>     @shelf.write directly (escape-hatch for tests where dispatch
>>     isn't the subject — match the production
>>     `as record @def + @shelf.write` shape and label the bypass).
>>
>> Removing this stub is gated on all four scripted suites (banking,
>> slack, workspace, travel) migrating off bucket-shape pre-seeding.
exe @stateWithResolved(record, handle, payload) = [
  => @emptyStateShape()
]

>> DEPRECATED — see @stateWithResolved.
exe @stateResolvedAndExtracted(record, handle, recordValue, extractName, extractSchema, extractValue) = [
  let @previewFields = @extractValue.mx.keys ?? []
  => {
    extracted: {
      "@extractName": {
        provenance: "extracted",
        schema_name: @extractSchema,
        preview_fields: @previewFields,
        value: @extractValue
      }
    },
    derived: {},
    extract_sources: {}
  }
]

>> Internal helper — returns the post-Stage-B empty state shape (no
>> `resolved`, no `capabilities`).
exe @emptyStateShape() = [
  => { extracted: {}, derived: {}, extract_sources: {} }
]

export {
  @stateWithExtracted,
  @stateWithDerived,
  @stateWithResolved,
  @stateResolvedAndExtracted
}
